  <bioghist id="aspace_bce4524de0345d1df2bfa0b0dccc72bc">
    <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
<p>Clifton Mines was located in Clifton, St. Lawrence Co., New York. The company and the railroad it owned operated for only a few years, 1864-1870. The ore bed was later bought (1942) and mining operations revived in 1944 by the M.A. Hanna Co.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_95843d8f3533808e97603271db3745c9">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Photographs, clippings and magazine articles, and typescripts of newspaper articles ca.1867-ca.1941 concerning the Clifton Iron Co., St. Lawrence County, New York. Also, certificates of increase of capital stock, 1864, 1868; consent to mortgage, 1866; and typescripts of the certificate of incorporation and financial documents.</p>  </scopecontent>
